Description: fullscreen transparent drawing overlay for X11
 zPen creates a transparent fullscreen layer over the desktop, letting
 you annotate, sketch, and highlight anything on screen. It supports
 freehand pen strokes, lines, arrows, rectangles, circles, braces,
 brackets, blur brush, text, numbered step markers, and on-the-fly
 colour and thickness changes.
 .
 It can also capture screen regions to PNG (saved under ~/.zpen/) or
 to the clipboard, paste images from the clipboard, and run OCR on a
 selected region (requires tesseract-ocr) with the result copied to
 the clipboard.
 .
 zPen targets X11 desktops with a compositor for transparency. Wayland
 sessions can use it via XWayland.
